'''Madrid''' is the capital and most populous city of Spain. It sits on the Manzanares river in the centre of the Iberian Peninsula and is the country's political, economic, and cultural heart.

The city is home to the Spanish royal family, national government institutions, and a dense concentration of museums. The [[Museo del Prado]], Reina Sofía, and Thyssen-Bornemisza together form its renowned Golden Triangle of Art.
